<?php $slug = 'binance-uk-derivatives-class-action'; require __DIR__.'/_header.php'; ?>

<p class="ko">영국 투자자 약 1,700명이 세계 최대 가상자산 거래소 바이낸스와 창업자 자오창펑(CZ)을 상대로 런던 고등법원(High Court)에 집단소송을 제기했다고 <strong>crypto.news</strong>와 <strong>사우스차이나모닝포스트(SCMP)</strong>가 전했다. 청구액은 최소 1억5,000만 파운드(약 2억 달러)로, 규제 인가 없이 위험한 파생상품을 판매해 손실을 입혔다는 주장이 핵심이다.</p>
  <p class="en">About 1,700 UK investors have filed a class action against Binance, the world's largest crypto exchange, and its founder Changpeng Zhao (CZ) in London's High Court, <strong>crypto.news</strong> and the <strong>South China Morning Post (SCMP)</strong> reported. The claim seeks at least £150 million (about $200 million), and its core allegation is that Binance sold risky derivatives without regulatory authorization and thereby caused losses.</p>
  <p class="ja">英国の投資家約1,700人が、世界最大の暗号資産取引所Binanceと創業者の趙長鵬(CZ)を相手取り、ロンドン高等法院(High Court)に集団訴訟を提起したと<strong>crypto.news</strong>と<strong>サウスチャイナ・モーニング・ポスト(SCMP)</strong>が伝えた。請求額は最低1億5,000万ポンド(約2億ドル)で、規制認可なしに危険なデリバティブを販売し損失を与えたという主張が核心だ。</p>
  <p class="es">Unos 1.700 inversores del Reino Unido han presentado una demanda colectiva contra Binance, el mayor exchange cripto del mundo, y su fundador Changpeng Zhao (CZ) ante el Tribunal Superior (High Court) de Londres, informaron <strong>crypto.news</strong> y el <strong>South China Morning Post (SCMP)</strong>. La demanda reclama al menos 150 millones de libras (unos 200 millones de dólares), y su alegación central es que Binance vendió derivados de riesgo sin autorización regulatoria y con ello causó pérdidas.</p>
  <p class="de">Rund 1.700 britische Anleger haben vor dem Londoner High Court eine Sammelklage gegen Binance, die größte Krypto-Börse der Welt, und ihren Gründer Changpeng Zhao (CZ) eingereicht, berichteten <strong>crypto.news</strong> und die <strong>South China Morning Post (SCMP)</strong>. Die Klage fordert mindestens 150 Millionen Pfund (etwa 200 Millionen Dollar); ihr zentraler Vorwurf ist, dass Binance riskante Derivate ohne regulatorische Zulassung verkaufte und dadurch Verluste verursachte.</p>

